120
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:30,240
They were just working.

121
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,450
They are co-workers.

122
00:08:32,450 --> 00:08:34,510
Nothing more, nothing less.

123
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:39,350
But I'm never wrong.

124
00:08:39,350 --> 00:08:40,410
How odd.

125
00:08:40,410 --> 00:08:41,510
Really?

126
00:08:41,950 --> 00:08:45,080
They did nothing outside work?

127
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,480
Nothing.

128
00:08:49,350 --> 00:08:50,650
Okay...

129
00:08:59,510 --> 00:09:02,610
No, they're not dating.

130
00:09:02,610 --> 00:09:05,740
They're just co-workers.

131
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,140
Co-workers.

132
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:29,350
Oh, Eunsu's not answering her phone.

133
00:09:29,950 --> 00:09:33,240
I should call Jiwan, then.

134
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:35,040
Yes, of course.

135
00:09:39,710 --> 00:09:40,740
Jiwan.

136
00:09:40,750 --> 00:09:41,780
Hi, Yeongju.

137
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:46,080
Are you with Eunsu right now?

138
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:46,940
No.

139
00:09:46,950 --> 00:09:49,010
