00:19:35,510 --> 00:19:37,280
Why did you drag me out from there?

287
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:38,780
Didn't you hear what she said?

288
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:39,840
She wasn't wrong.

289
00:19:39,850 --> 00:19:41,580
Being yelled at is a process of learning.

290
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:43,810
It's not just anyone. It's your little sister.

291
00:19:43,810 --> 00:19:45,710
How can you be neutral about your sister?

292
00:19:45,710 --> 00:19:46,350
How could you do that?

293
00:19:46,350 --> 00:19:48,110
Then, what will you say?

294
00:19:48,110 --> 00:19:49,480
You're going to use your father's position

295
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:50,740
and threaten Ms. Bae?

296
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:52,880
Why can't I use my father's position?

297
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:55,380
Everyone knows I'm the owner's son.

298
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:56,840
What about Eunsu, then?

299
00:19:57,550 --> 00:19:58,880
You want people to think

300
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:00,210
she got hired because of you?

301
00:20:00,210 --> 00:20:01,280
But that's not true.

302
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:03,040
When everyone says it's true, it will seem so

303
00:20:03,050 --> 00:20:04,240
even if it isn't.

304
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:05,010
Kim Jiwan!

305
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:06,550
I'm angrier than you!

306
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:09,140
Don't you know your doing this puts

307
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:10,780
Eunsu at a more difficult position?

308
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,550
But I can't just sit and watch.

309
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:17,110
Eunsu will take care of it.

310
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:20,880
She can take care of it by herself.

311
00:20:21,710 --> 00:20:24,450
Let's not get involved, making it more difficult.

312
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:29,910
I've seen plenty of kids like you

313
00:20:29,910 --> 00:20:31,410
who get hired using connections.

314
00:20:31,410 --> 00:20:33,610
Do you know how annoying it is to have

315
00:20:33,610 --> 00:20:35,480
the likes of you ruin our reputation?

316
00:20:36,010 --> 00:20:36,880
Get out!

317
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,910
You don't need to work here.

318
00:20:38,910 --> 00:20:40,780
You have great connections. Why work at all?

319
00:20:40,780 --> 00:20:43,310
You'll get paid and get promoted anyway.

320
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:47,010
I said get out!

321
00:20:47,010 --> 00:20:48,880
Are you deaf?

322
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:55,240
What are you doing?

323
00:20:55,910 --> 00:20:58,080
Please check these again.

324
00:21:00,750 --> 00:21:03,740
I'll learn and get getter.

325
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:05,010
I'll work harder to make up

326
00:21:05,010 --> 00:21:06,710
for my shortcomings.

327
00:21:06,710 --> 00:21:08,280
I'll study all night if I don't know something,

328
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:09,740
so I can catch up very quickly.

329
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:11,010
But...

330
00:21:13,810 --> 00:21:15,010
Don't insult me for something

331
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:16,580
that's not work-related.

332
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:23,210
I won the contest fair and square.

333
00:21:23,210 --> 00:21:26,210
I never relied on anyone to get this job.

334
00:21:26,210 --> 00:21:26,780
Hey!

335
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:29,080
And...

336
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:31,350
I checked them dozens of times.

337
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:33,010
There are no typos.

338
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:39,280
Please check them again.

339
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:56,380
I'll check them, and we'll talk again.

340
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:24,910
You're really worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

341
00:22:27,410 --> 00:22:29,450
It's hard for me to let it go easily,

342
00:22:29,450 --> 00:22:31,410
since she's my little sister and all.

343
00:22:31,410 --> 00:22:34,010
Eunsu's doing a good job.

344
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:36,410
She's worthy of being your sister.

345
00:22:37,550 --> 00:22:38,710
Thank you.

346
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:41,240
But I'm worried.

347
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:45,010
Rumors can be quite vicious.

348
00:22:46,650 --> 00:22:49,380
Rumors are just rumors.

349
00:22:50,250 --> 00:22:54,240
Eunsu will get though it.

350
00:22:54,250 --> 00:22:56,240
Just like you did.

351
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:59,110
How do you know so well?

352
00:22:59,110 --> 00:23:01,450
I can tell.

353
00:23:01,450 --> 00:23:03,280
You two are very similar.

354
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:05,580
But...

355
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:09,040
How did you know I was here?

356
00:23:12,710 --> 00:23:14,110
Are you following me around?

357
00:23:14,110 --> 00:23:15,240
Follow...

358
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:31,350
Jiwan, shouldn't you get back to work?

359
00:23:43,650 --> 00:23:45,550
It's a personal loan.

360
00:23:47,850 --> 00:23:51,180
You've met this month's quota.

361
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:52,740
Good job.

362
00:23:59,350 --> 00:24:00,380
Honey.

363
00:24:00,380 --> 00:24:01,310
Honey, I'm home.

364
00:24:01,310 --> 00:24:02,610
What is it?

365
00:24:02,610 --> 00:24:04,110
You're home?

366
00:24:04,110 --> 00:24:06,580
Oh, my, honey, what are you doing?

367
00:24:06,580 --> 00:24:07,510
What's going on?

368
00:24:07,510 --> 00:24:09,240
Take that off right now.

369
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:13,910
Just sit here. I'm almost done.

370
00:24:14,750 --> 00:24:16,040
Don't come in.

371
00:24:16,050 --> 00:24:17,280
Don't even come near.

372
00:24:17,280 --> 00:24:18,980
I'm going to finish what I started.

373
00:24:20,010 --> 00:24:21,650
Finish what?

374
00:24:21,650 --> 00:24:25,510
He's going to leave me lots of dishes to wash.

375
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:29,810
What?

376
00:24:36,380 --> 00:24:38,140
Red ginseng?

377
00:24:41,710 --> 00:24:44,610
Happy Marriage Day
Thank you. I'm sorry!

378
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:48,510
Why couldn't he write a bit more?

379
00:24:48,510 --> 00:24:51,080
One line? That's it?

380
00:24:57,910 --> 00:25:00,580
Oh, there's so much to eat.

381
00:25:00,580 --> 00:25:01,910
Right?

382
00:25:01,910 --> 00:25:03,310
Here.

383
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:04,780
- Enjoy. 
 - Okay.

384
00:25:10,310 --> 00:25:11,840
It looks good.

385
00:25:13,710 --> 00:25:15,180
Let me see...

386
00:25:19,010 --> 00:25:22,010
You bought this at the market, right?

387
00:25:22,950 --> 00:25:26,980
And this came from Yeongcheol's Side Dishes.

388
00:25:26,980 --> 00:25:28,510
Hansik's makes better

389
00:25:28,510 --> 00:25:30,110
side dishes than Yeongcheol's.

390
00:25:30,110 --> 00:25:31,310
This was $5, right?

391
00:25:31,310 --> 00:25:33,450
At Hansik's, it's $4.

392
00:25:34,850 --> 00:25:36,940
If you keep doing this,

393
00:25:36,950 --> 00:25:39,010
I won't want to do this for you again.

394
00:25:41,110 --> 00:25:43,610
Oh, really? Why, I'm sorry, honey.

395
00:25:43,610 --> 00:25:47,840
So don't ever do this again, okay?

396
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:49,380
Okay.

397
00:25:49,380 --> 00:25:52,450
Now that you said that, I know I must.

398
00:25:53,050 --> 00:25:54,980
Honey, what's going on?

399
00:25:54,980 --> 00:25:56,350
Did something nice happen today?

400
00:25:56,350 --> 00:25:58,810
A gift and dinner? What is it?

401
00:25:58,810 --> 00:26:02,240
I can't buy you luxury brand bags anymore,

402
00:26:02,250 --> 00:26:04,740
so I have to look after your health.

403
00:26:04,750 --> 00:26:08,140
If you get sick, I'll be the one who suffers.

404
00:26:09,010 --> 00:26:10,510
Oh, whatever.

405
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:18,710
When your job gets too hard, you must quit.

406
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:20,510
Just promise me that.

407
00:26:20,510 --> 00:26:22,580
It's not like you're having it easy.

408
00:26:22,580 --> 00:26:24,240
They must be pressuring you

409
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:25,650
to meet the quota.

410
00:26:25,650 --> 00:26:26,610
No.

411
00:26:26,610 --> 00:26:28,550
I've already met this month's quota.

412
00:26:28,550 --> 00:26:30,550
I won't have to worry about it for a while.

413
00:26:30,550 --> 00:26:31,940
Really?

414
00:26:31,950 --> 00:26:32,980
Honey, I'm so happy for you!

415
00:26:32,980 --> 00:26:36,210
That's great! I'm so happy for you.

416
00:26:37,310 --> 00:26:37,940
Don't worry.

417
00:26:37,950 --> 00:26:39,310
You two are home already?

418
00:26:39,810 --> 00:26:41,180
Dad, you came home earl...

419
00:26:44,750 --> 00:26:46,040
Please continue.

420
00:26:46,050 --> 00:26:47,350
I'll leave you two alone.

421
00:26:47,350 --> 00:26:48,480
Don't say that.

422
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:50,110
Come and have dinner.

423
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:52,680
It looks like I might get a little sibling.

424
00:26:53,810 --> 00:26:55,180
What did she say?

425
00:26:56,110 --> 00:26:58,610
Maybe she feels better now.

426
00:26:58,610 --> 00:27:00,110
She didn't tell you what

427
00:27:00,110 --> 00:27:01,940
the other night was about, did she?

428
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:03,680
Minja.

429
00:27:04,210 --> 00:27:07,880
Don't worry about your kid tonight

430
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,710
and enjoy your dinner.

431
00:27:10,550 --> 00:27:12,580
Okay, Jaecheol.

432
00:27:13,110 --> 00:27:14,010
You eat, too.

433
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:15,280
Try them.

434
00:27:41,180 --> 00:27:45,180
Hyeondo, I'm used to drinking soju by itself,

435
00:27:45,180 --> 00:27:47,680
but you're all about style,

436
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:49,650
so why are you drinking like this?

437
00:27:50,050 --> 00:27:51,210
If your mom sees you,

438
00:27:51,210 --> 00:27:53,450
she'll say it's because you take after me.

439
00:27:55,610 --> 00:27:58,240
Is something bothering you?

440
00:27:59,610 --> 00:28:02,840
Oh, you gave me back my car,

441
00:28:02,850 --> 00:28:04,880
so why would anything bother me?

442
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:08,180
But if you gave me back my credit card...

443
00:28:08,180 --> 00:28:11,080
Really? I can take your car away again.

444
00:28:12,750 --> 00:28:13,780
You want it?

445
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:16,810
Really?

446
00:28:16,810 --> 00:28:19,980
Now, I'm sure there's something bothering you.

447
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:31,040
Have you ever held yourself back for mom?

448
00:28:31,050 --> 00:28:33,140
I do that every day.

449
00:28:34,850 --> 00:28:40,380
Doing nothing for the sake of the other person.

450
00:28:40,380 --> 00:28:41,610
How does that make sense?

451
00:28:44,610 --> 00:28:47,550
I did something for someone,

452
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:51,450
but it turned out, I did it for myself.

453
00:28:52,050 --> 00:28:53,550
Well...

454
00:28:53,550 --> 00:28:55,180
I'm not sure who the other person is, but

455
00:28:55,180 --> 00:29:00,210
she's amazing for making you think this way.

456
00:29:02,510 --> 00:29:04,740
If it took that much thought to decide,

457
00:29:04,750 --> 00:29:08,110
whatever that is, you're doing it for her.

458
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:09,810
The girl you're seeing right now,

459
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:12,310
if she makes you think this hard,

460
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:15,010
she must be worth it. Yes.

461
00:29:15,010 --> 00:29:17,310
I don't know who it is, but I'm all for her,

462
00:29:17,310 --> 00:29:19,550
so just bring her and let me meet her.

463
00:29:20,180 --> 00:29:21,610
Okay.

464
00:29:21,610 --> 00:29:23,180
I'll bring her home soon to meet you.

465
00:29:24,350 --> 00:29:26,810
If you used half the energy you use on that girl

466
00:29:26,810 --> 00:29:28,650
at work, you'd be doing twice as better.

467
00:29:29,580 --> 00:29:33,040
That was why I married your mom so early.

468
00:29:33,050 --> 00:29:34,840
So I can focus on work.

469
00:29:36,510 --> 00:29:40,910
What about mom do you love so much?

470
00:29:40,910 --> 00:29:43,210
I mean, she's my mom, so I put up with her,

471
00:29:43,210 --> 00:29:44,810
but if she were my wife, well...

472
00:29:44,810 --> 00:29:48,510
Stay away from my wife!

473
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:50,450
You can't see how attractive she is

474
00:29:50,450 --> 00:29:51,680
because she's your mom.

475
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:55,710
I would never get sick of that woman.

476
00:29:55,710 --> 00:30:00,350
Like mom said, she is your first and only love?

477
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:02,880
An unrealistically hopeless romantic

478
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:04,550
who married his first love?

479
00:30:04,550 --> 00:30:05,740
Don't you dare!

480
00:30:05,750 --> 00:30:07,480
Don't drink too much. Go to bed.

481
00:30:08,010 --> 00:30:09,880
Whoa, you are!

482
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,740
Mom was telling the truth.

483
00:30:11,750 --> 00:30:13,350
You're like one of the handful of men

484
00:30:13,350 --> 00:30:15,010
whose been with only one woman!

485
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:20,080
Goodnight, Mr. Hopeless Romantic!

486
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:09,010
Hi.

487
00:31:09,780 --> 00:31:12,580
Are you all right?

488
00:31:12,580 --> 00:31:13,650
Of course.

489
00:31:13,650 --> 00:31:16,480
Ms. Bae gave me a compliment today.

490
00:31:20,150 --> 00:31:22,550
I'm going to work even harder.

491
00:31:23,310 --> 00:31:27,080
I'm not going to use inexperience as an excuse.

492
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:30,740
I'm going to work harder, and prove to them

493
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:33,880
I won the contest with my talent,

494
00:31:34,780 --> 00:31:39,450
so will you watch me from afar?

495
00:31:41,350 --> 00:31:44,380
Don't be too friendly, don't try to step up.

496
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:48,040
If you keep trying to help me,

497
00:31:48,050 --> 00:31:50,080
I'd want to rely on you.

498
00:31:51,850 --> 00:31:53,080
Sure.

499
00:31:54,710 --> 00:31:57,780
I won't be friendly at work anymore.

500
00:31:58,610 --> 00:32:00,610
You're not angry, are you?

501
00:32:01,780 --> 00:32:03,010
I'm hanging up.

502
00:32:11,210 --> 00:32:13,080
He is angry.

503
00:32:22,380 --> 00:32:24,110
Excuse me.

504
00:32:24,110 --> 00:32:25,010
Who are you?

505
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:26,980
It's okay.

506
00:32:26,980 --> 00:32:28,080
Oh.

507
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:30,450
Hello, Mr. Shin.

508
00:32:30,450 --> 00:32:32,550
We meet again.

509
00:32:33,950 --> 00:32:37,580
It's me. Haengsuk.

510
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:40,380
We met in front of Seonhui's restaurant.

511
00:32:40,380 --> 00:32:42,840
Oh, hello.

512
00:32:45,150 --> 00:32:48,610
I thought it might be you.

513
00:32:48,610 --> 00:32:51,240
What brings you here?

514
00:32:52,750 --> 00:32:53,980
Actually,

515
00:32:53,980 --> 00:32:57,410
I've been working near here for a while now.

516
00:32:58,180 --> 00:33:01,580
At the porridge place over there.

517
00:33:02,650 --> 00:33:04,550
Please drop by sometime.

518
00:33:04,550 --> 00:33:08,740
I'll make you delicious porridge.

519
00:33:08,750 --> 00:33:10,510
I'll try.

520
00:33:10,510 --> 00:33:12,910
Goodbye.

521
00:33:21,410 --> 00:33:26,210
Front and back, he's my type.

522
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:34,940
Front and back, he's just dark everywhere.

523
00:33:34,950 --> 00:33:36,580
This customer?

524
00:33:36,580 --> 00:33:37,550
Yes?

525
00:33:39,580 --> 00:33:42,010
Oh, the yam porridge?

526
00:33:42,010 --> 00:33:43,880
He paid.

527
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:45,650
This customer,

528
00:33:46,750 --> 00:33:48,480
why do you think he didn't finish it?

529
00:33:49,010 --> 00:33:51,810
Because he didn't want to finish it.

530
00:33:51,810 --> 00:33:53,680
Why didn't he want to finish it?

531
00:33:53,680 --> 00:33:56,240
How would I know?

532
00:33:56,250 --> 00:33:59,040
Maybe he was full, or maybe it tasted...

533
00:34:03,250 --> 00:34:07,040
Next time, ask why they didn't finish.

534
00:34:07,050 --> 00:34:08,180
Yes, sir.

535
00:34:35,980 --> 00:34:36,910
Whoa.

536
00:34:36,910 --> 00:34:38,910
What took you so long?

537
00:34:38,910 --> 00:34:39,580
Oh, right.

538
00:34:39,580 --> 00:34:42,180
You tend to come here in the evening.

539
00:34:43,580 --> 00:34:45,040
Why did you come back?

540
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:47,140
Because I get more ideas when I come here.

541
00:34:47,150 --> 00:34:49,080
For some reason, I can focus better.

542
00:34:49,080 --> 00:34:50,350
Maybe they have good feng shui.

543
00:34:50,850 --> 00:34:54,350
When I see you, I don't want to work anymore.

544
00:34:55,180 --> 00:34:58,240
Don't stay stuff like that in front of me.

545
00:34:58,250 --> 00:34:59,740
I have a temper, too, if I'm mad.

546
00:34:59,750 --> 00:35:02,080
Say it to my face!

547
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:04,180
A man shouldn't mumble.

548
00:35:04,750 --> 00:35:07,550
Why would she say that? How offensive.

549
00:35:07,550 --> 00:35:09,740
And a writer shouldn't be a sexist.

550
00:35:09,750 --> 00:35:11,810
No wonder people say her script is old.

551
00:35:11,810 --> 00:35:13,610
I can hear you.

552
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:18,310
Jiwan!

553
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:20,680
Hi.

554
00:35:21,250 --> 00:35:23,010
Oh, he looks nice in a suit.

555
00:35:23,010 --> 00:35:24,280
You're here again?

556
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:26,140
This place must be great for writing.

557
00:35:26,910 --> 00:35:28,880
By the way, who is he?

558
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:30,010
Your boyfriend?

559
00:35:30,010 --> 00:35:30,740
No.

560
00:35:30,750 --> 00:35:31,680
Hello.

561
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:33,580
I'm Yeongju's friend's older brother, Kim Jiwan.

562
00:35:33,580 --> 00:35:35,810
Hello, I'm Heo Seonggeun.

563
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:37,210
It's nice to meet you.

564
00:35:37,810 --> 00:35:39,310
He's not my boyfriend.

565
